# GitNexus setup notes for this machine:
# - This is an older 8GB RAM desktop, so the main matrix index should stay
#   focused on matrix itself.
# - Reference repos under _ref/ are indexed as separate GitNexus repos
#   (agno, EvoSkill, autoresearch, mempalace, auto-rag-optimizer,
#   hermes-agent including tinker-atropos). Do not pull them into matrix.
# - TREK is intentionally not indexed.
# - Local GitNexus package tuning was added for future runs:
#   GITNEXUS_PARSE_WORKERS=<n>, GITNEXUS_PARSE_TIMEOUT_MS=<ms>,
#   GITNEXUS_PARSE_SUB_BATCH_SIZE=<n>, GITNEXUS_HEAP_MB=<mb>,
#   GITNEXUS_STACK_KB=<kb>, GITNEXUS_EMBEDDING_BATCH_SIZE=<n>.
#   Defaults stay fast; use lower workers/batch/heap only if RAM or swap hurts.
_ref/

# Defensive excludes for generated dependencies, virtualenvs, caches, and build
# outputs. GitNexus normally respects .gitignore; keep these here too so a
# future run cannot accidentally ingest heavy local artifacts.
node_modules/
.venv/
**/.venv/
vendor/
**/vendor/
target/
**/target/
.next/
**/.next/
.turbo/
**/.turbo/
.cache/
**/.cache/
__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.log
